When we get into a traffic jam, and we are in a hurry to a VIP client, or to a training, or a seminar, or to a hard-line manager,

04:27.000 --> 04:31.000
what is bad in a traffic jam at this moment?

04:31.000 --> 04:35.000
We are impatient, of course.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
We are irritated, of course.

04:37.000 --> 04:39.000
We can't change anything, of course.

04:39.000 --> 04:43.000
We curse this city, this place where we got.

04:43.000 --> 04:45.000
It's all right.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
But you can't leave the car.

04:47.000 --> 04:50.000
You can't run out of the traffic jam.

04:51.000 --> 04:58.000
And so, in order to come to a VIP client in a good mood, to come to the manager on the carpet,

04:58.000 --> 05:05.000
having a situation, you need to maintain a joyful, optimistic state and mood.

05:05.000 --> 05:12.000
To be honest, I noticed this before, when people ran out of the traffic jam, argued, quarreled with each other, someone blushed, someone blushed.

05:12.000 --> 05:17.000
Now, in general, Muscovites have already become, and in general, in any cities, people have become more experienced.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.000
They understand that they can't get out of the traffic jam.

05:19.000 --> 05:22.000
And they say to themselves, what's good about the traffic jam?

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
Let's talk about the advantages that the traffic jam gives.

05:24.000 --> 05:29.000
Well, the first point is that you can better prepare for a meeting with a VIP client.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.000
We have time.

05:31.000 --> 05:35.000
Naturally, we will call him in advance, so that, of course, we will be late.

05:35.000 --> 05:40.000
You can prepare for a meeting with a manager.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
These are the advantages.

05:42.000 --> 05:48.000
You can think about who you can call at this moment, having obtained additional information.

05:48.000 --> 05:52.000
If you did it, and we are still in the traffic jam, you can call your parents.

05:52.000 --> 05:58.000
You haven't called them for six months, you've already forgotten that your mother is waiting for your call.

05:58.000 --> 06:03.000
It's very good for women to call their child and say some important words.

06:03.000 --> 06:09.000
Many people are now in the traffic jam, they turn on audio books, listen to some important texts.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
I, for example, noticed that they listen to Dostoevsky well.

06:12.000 --> 06:15.000
I noticed that foreign languages are taught in the traffic jam.

06:15.000 --> 06:22.000
Look how much good can be done in the traffic jam if we remember a positive approach.

06:22.000 --> 06:24.000
Another situation.

06:24.000 --> 06:29.000
We gave a large amount of money to a friend a few years ago.

06:29.000 --> 06:35.000
And he still looks us in the eye and says, I can't give such serious money.

06:35.000 --> 06:38.000
Of course, what is unpleasant for us in this situation?

06:38.000 --> 06:43.000
We made a mistake again. We lost money, probably two times.

06:43.000 --> 06:47.000
We say some unpleasant words to ourselves, blaming ourselves, why did I do it?

06:47.000 --> 06:49.000
A close person blames you.

06:49.000 --> 06:53.000
Remember, we wanted to buy it, and you gave money to your friend.

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
The situation has already gone.

06:55.000 --> 07:00.000
And to maintain a good relationship with a friend and a close person,

07:00.000 --> 07:05.000
and to maintain an optimistic mood and a good attitude to people,

07:05.000 --> 07:08.000
what is good in the fact that we gave money to the debt.

07:08.000 --> 07:11.000
Let's focus on the positives.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
First, we helped a person.

07:14.000 --> 07:22.000
Second, life and fate have shown us that money is not so important.

07:22.000 --> 07:28.000
Help and what we were then, to help another, is probably more important.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
And the third point, let's make a conclusion that we need to work more intensively to compensate for the money lost.

07:34.000 --> 07:42.000
In every situation, even the most difficult, there is an advantage.

07:42.000 --> 07:50.000
It is more profitable for us to highlight the advantages, because it gives energy and strength.

07:50.000 --> 07:58.000
And it is not profitable for us to focus on the minuses.

07:58.000 --> 08:04.000
Because the minuses reduce our energy, reduce our self-esteem, make us weaker.

08:04.000 --> 08:14.000
Moreover, we know that if we are optimistic, happy people come to us, positive events stick to us.

08:14.000 --> 08:27.000
If we concentrate on the minuses, sad people come to us, and not very positive, not very happy events come to us.

08:28.000 --> 08:36.000
In addition to the fact that any situation can be assessed and perceived from the side of pluses or minuses,

08:36.000 --> 08:46.000
it is also important to understand that a person can also be perceived either from the side of his strong bright qualities or from the side of his shortcomings.

08:46.000 --> 08:52.000
Let's think, for example, now about that person, think about you, who is unpleasant to you.

08:52.000 --> 08:57.000
You meet him in the corridor, in the company, you try to avoid communicating with him.

08:57.000 --> 09:04.000
A few days ago there was a conflict with a colleague, and you are not pleased to see this person.

09:04.000 --> 09:09.000
Think about the shortcomings he showed in himself, he showed in the conflict.

09:09.000 --> 09:14.000
The first, probably, is irritation. He said to you unfair words.

09:14.000 --> 09:17.000
He criticized you publicly, that it was offensive.

09:17.000 --> 09:21.000
You tried, you made a project, and suddenly such criticism is undeserved.

09:21.000 --> 09:27.000
Maybe he was self-assertive, maybe he competed with you.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
All this is unpleasant.

09:29.000 --> 09:41.000
But in order to maintain long-term relations, first of all, we need to remember the advantages, the strong, interesting qualities for us, even of the person who criticizes us.

09:41.000 --> 09:51.000
The first point I would like to note is the position of a positive approach, which gives us enlightened optimism, which we are now talking about.

09:51.000 --> 10:03.000
A critic points out our mistakes. A critic, in fact, cares about our professional improvement, our development.

10:04.000 --> 10:08.000
A person who shows irritation is usually open.

10:08.000 --> 10:17.000
And, to be honest, I see a huge advantage in this. He won't hit you in the back, he won't sit down until this political moment, he will say what he doesn't like.

10:17.000 --> 10:25.000
A person who is excited is also open, and, as a rule, we understand him better, because he sincerely expresses his point of view.

10:25.000 --> 10:27.000
Look at the advantages.

10:27.000 --> 10:37.000
And the main thing, according to this situation, is that a critic, and the one who does not evaluate us very positively, cares about our further development.

10:37.000 --> 10:43.000
We know, for example, a client. Love the client's objections. You need to love the client's objections.

10:43.000 --> 10:59.000
The client develops us, makes us learn new things. If there are no objections, no interest in our product or service, the objections develop the business.

10:59.000 --> 11:08.000
Look at the advantages of a critic, a demanding client. The same is true here.

11:09.000 --> 11:25.000
But there is another point. Not only are we dissatisfied and we are not pleased, it is understandable when we are criticized, but we also do interesting internal work when we criticize ourselves.

11:25.000 --> 11:36.000
We did something, we invested in the development of the project, we reported, presented this project, and everyone liked it.

11:36.000 --> 11:44.000
We come home and start criticizing ourselves. This is bad, I didn't finish it, I was in a hurry, this is probably a mistake.

11:44.000 --> 11:53.000
And we fall asleep in the evening with a heavy feeling. I noticed that clients sometimes say that.

11:53.000 --> 12:00.000
And in general, I am nobody and my name is nothing. We destroy ourselves to the end. Is that right?

12:00.000 --> 12:04.000
But from the point of view of a positive approach, it is absolutely wrong.

12:05.000 --> 12:19.000
Of course, we know about our shortcomings. If we forgot them for a while, remember how we were scolded as children, our mother criticized us, or our grandmother, or our first teacher, or at the institute.

12:19.000 --> 12:34.000
If you are so lucky that your mother didn't criticize, but only praised, and your first teacher praised, and at the institute we were praised, then of course there will be a close person, whether it is a spouse or a child, who will finally start criticizing us.

12:34.000 --> 12:53.000
Of course, we remember or are reminded of our shortcomings. But if we only remember about shortcomings, there is uncertainty, anxiety, we don't want to do anything, and it is not beneficial to us, because we strive for success.

12:53.000 --> 13:05.000
Let's think about our advantages, about our strong, bright, winning sides. For example, each of our shortcomings can be translated into advantages.

13:05.000 --> 13:15.000
For example, our sense of guilt. We feel guilt. To be honest, it is a shortcoming. But let's look at it from the perspective of advantages.

13:15.000 --> 13:29.000
This is a high demand for yourself, this is a desire to work better and better, this is an ability to put into practice to feel that this success is really deserved.

13:29.000 --> 13:43.000
It happens that a person says, no, I'm fine, but I'm afraid, I'm very afraid to go to the center, I'm afraid of any public performance. I see an advantage in this, it's a zone of close development.

13:43.000 --> 13:54.000
I always say, go to the center more often, tell anecdotes, funny stories to get used to this public role. I noticed this feature.

13:55.000 --> 14:15.000
When a person is afraid to go to the center, but then overcomes himself, he tells very interesting things, he is very deep, because he has overcome himself, and the content that appears from him, not only professional, but also personal, is always interesting to others.

14:16.000 --> 14:22.000
Because it is always interesting to other people how another person lives, how he overcomes difficulties.

14:23.000 --> 14:31.000
I also noticed this feature. Sometimes in groups people say, you know, there is another quality, and I have it, it is laziness.

14:31.000 --> 14:44.000
Most often women say this. I ask, what time do you get up? Well, at 5-6 am. What do you do? I work. And after work? You know, I help my husband's parents, help my parents, children, husband.

14:45.000 --> 14:52.000
And you say I'm lazy about myself. A woman says, well, yes, in general, frankly, I think that I'm probably lazy, I could work more.

14:53.000 --> 15:01.000
In fact, laziness should also be treated well. Barbara Bylska, for example, says that a lazy woman is a feminine woman.

15:02.000 --> 15:14.000
A lazy person, as men say, is a person who builds a civilization, who thinks not how to do it intensively, but how to do it more optimally, logistically correctly.

15:14.000 --> 15:23.000
A lazy person, as a rule, is a good philosopher. Remember our Oblomov, who lay on the couch and based on his life a classic novel was built.

15:24.000 --> 15:36.000
Lazy people are finally good people. Lazy people are more loved in our culture because they are kind, positive, relaxed, soft, than hard-working people.

15:36.000 --> 15:44.000
While we are not very used to the fact that a person works, does not spare himself, he is tough, a woman becomes tough in business.

15:45.000 --> 15:52.000
I think, of course, there will come a time when we will get used to it. But look at what a hell I sang to such a quality as laziness.

15:53.000 --> 16:09.000
Therefore, in the morning, instead of scolding yourself, and in the evening, instead of scolding yourself, you need to tell yourself what strong qualities you have, what winning advantages you will sell in business.

16:09.000 --> 16:23.000
And in the evening you need to say what you have done or did during the day, and, of course, praise yourself for the energy, for the intensity in which you are throwing yourself now.

16:24.000 --> 16:32.000
I draw a conclusion. So, dear friends, a positive approach, to be honest, is a technology of enlightened optimism.

16:33.000 --> 16:42.000
This is not the optimism when they say, everything is fine, think only about the good. No, this is what we know, that not everything is fine.

16:42.000 --> 16:55.000
In every situation, in every person, and in us too, there are difficult, difficult sides, but in every situation there are joyful, easy features and conditions.

16:55.000 --> 17:17.000
We will remember what obstacles there are and we will try to overcome them. And we will remember that energy, ability to work, self-confidence appears when we highlight our own advantages, when we communicate with another person highlighting his advantages.

17:17.000 --> 17:27.000
And, to be honest, we do not get into a difficult, difficult situation, an impassable one, a traffic jam, for example, or money in debt.

17:27.000 --> 17:47.000
When we remember that this is also a life or professional lesson, and maybe in the future, in 5 or 20 years, we will remember this situation with gratitude, because it made us grow a new competence, a new quality.

17:47.000 --> 18:02.000
And, indeed, as our bard Andrei Bakarevich sings, difficulties make us stronger. We have another file where energy is bright, powerful, dense.

18:02.000 --> 18:22.000
I sometimes say, if I represent our qualities, our abilities, not as files, but as floors of a huge building, then the floor of the intellect is correct, bright, everything is put on shelves.

18:22.000 --> 18:40.000
And the floor where our feelings, emotions, and experiences are a bubbling stream, everything is mixed there. And, indeed, as a result of stress, someone becomes passive, apathetic, depression begins, you don't want anything.

18:40.000 --> 18:57.000
And, to be honest, one of the criteria, if you are happy that a client did not come to the meeting, is the result of burning out of stress. If you are happy that two weeks of January holidays are ahead, this can also be a result of burning out and fatigue.

18:57.000 --> 19:09.000
But there is another manifestation of stress on this floor, when we are overexcited, irritated, we start to fuss, we drop documents, we are in a hurry somewhere.

19:09.000 --> 19:26.000
And in Moscow offices there is such a thing, which only we have, office rabble, when people throw their mobile phones, papers, folders, when they run out, knock on the door, run in, scream, cry.

19:26.000 --> 19:43.000
I had a supervisor, who I observed, he periodically had such a cute feature, he grabbed a liquid crystal computer, threw it on the floor, tried to trample it. In a state of aggression, rabble, this excitement, it's all stress.

19:43.000 --> 20:00.000
Stress is all stress on this floor. It is an inability to cope with one's emotions and feelings. And at this moment, when we are excited or when we don't care, it's hard to persuade ourselves.

20:00.000 --> 20:16.000
Because a positive approach is, of course, a technology to persuade yourself. And when we are shaken, or when we don't care, it's hard to persuade yourself.

20:16.000 --> 20:30.000
Therefore, if you feel that this floor is burning with emotions, feelings, and worries, an effective technique is visualization.

20:30.000 --> 20:43.000
Then start with images, I will tell you now which ones, and then you will start to persuade yourself. Let's try.

20:44.000 --> 20:55.000
Imagine, please, that now, after viewing this training material, you have a trip to the dentist scheduled for a certain time.

20:55.000 --> 21:14.000
You drive up to the dental clinic, go up to the appropriate floor, you already feel the sounds, the appropriate smells, and approach the office where you often go to your doctor.

21:14.000 --> 21:27.000
You look at the clock, exactly at the time you are scheduled, look into the office, there is no one, but you have a good, friendly relationship with the doctor for a long time.

21:27.000 --> 21:40.000
You enter the office and sit in the dentist's chair. Imagine yourself in a dentist's chair. Usually, on the right, a little further, there is the favorite NAMI machine, which is called a drill machine.

21:40.000 --> 21:51.000
We still have some tension in relation to it, it doesn't hurt anymore, some painless injections are already being done, and yet we start to strain when we look at this iron tool.

21:51.000 --> 22:07.000
On the right are the tools with which the doctor will examine our oral cavity. And, foreseeing all these events, we begin to strain.

22:07.000 --> 22:21.000
The door opens, and behind, you feel, a young nurse comes up to you and says, oh, sorry, the doctor is sick, come tomorrow.

22:21.000 --> 22:38.000
What do you feel? I agreed, I allocated time, and the doctor did not even inform me that he was sick. But most people are sincerely happy if there is no acute pain.

22:38.000 --> 22:56.000
I told you that the visit, as if it happened, but the treatment itself is postponed for at least a day, there is still a day of calm existence. What was I talking about? I was talking about the image that arises and changes our state.

22:56.000 --> 23:12.000
I told you about the exercise of Kristallnachtschreiner. He says, as a result, do not live your life as if you are sitting in the chair of a dentist all the time. And maybe this traumatic event will not happen.

23:12.000 --> 23:30.000
Because we can visualize images that are unpleasant for ourselves, the future that will be now. And we can visualize the opposite, pleasant, positive, good images.

23:30.000 --> 23:48.000
For example, the image of a shelter is a good exercise that helps to calm down, especially for those people who communicate a lot at client work or for managers who have to manage a large number of people.

23:48.000 --> 24:05.000
Think, please, that each of us has our own shelter. This is some real space or a fictional, fantastic, virtual space, I don't know, maybe a spaceship to Mars.

24:05.000 --> 24:25.000
Some space where no one pulls us, no phones, no mobile, no stationary, no clients, no subordinates, no forced, intense, difficult, complex communication.

24:25.000 --> 24:40.000
You can do nothing there or do whatever you want. Someone listens to music, someone starts to draw in their imagination, someone composes poems.

24:40.000 --> 24:56.000
Think, please, about your fictional, virtual, or maybe real shelter and think about what you would do there now to calm down, relax and feel protected.

24:56.000 --> 25:08.000
If there is a real shelter, a dacha, or, for example, sometimes men say, this is a garage, I repair a car, and neither wife nor daughter goes there.

25:08.000 --> 25:25.000
You can do your business there. One of the interesting examples is that a lady in my group said, you know, I have a small apartment in a remote area, and no one knows about it.

25:25.000 --> 25:39.000
I come there and start drawing, just as I did when I was a child, because drawing calms me down. But really, since there is a lot of work and children and a husband at home, I don't have time to do it.

25:39.000 --> 25:52.000
There were cases when one of the young participants said, you know what kind of shelter I have? I have a private plane, and it really takes her, and she makes loops.

25:52.000 --> 26:06.000
And I was surprised, she was calm and careful in the group. I said, is it true? I can't believe you. And suddenly from another part of the room a young man said, yes, it's true.

26:06.000 --> 26:27.000
I said, how do you know? I'm her husband. I said, do you also fly on a plane and make loops? No, never. For this young lady, the participant of my seminar, it was the same shelter where she could feel the freedom of flight, the absence of any restrictions.

26:28.000 --> 26:43.000
This space, and everyone has their own. Someone sits behind the wheel and drives around Moscow at night. This is also a shelter, this is also an ability to feel a different state, a different image, to visualize yourself and your life in a different way.

26:43.000 --> 26:57.000
It can be a real situation or an invented situation. To be honest, for our biocomputer it doesn't matter. We really rest and calm down.

26:57.000 --> 27:16.000
Or it's the image that allows us to be in a different space for two or three, a maximum of five minutes. And to feel that we are calm again, that we have energy, that we want to live and work again.

27:16.000 --> 27:33.000
There are images that always give energy. This is the image of flight. I sometimes ask my participants, what kind of birds are you? Men often say, we are eagles. Women are swallows.

27:33.000 --> 27:47.000
