28:31.000 --> 28:51.000
You have a fireplace at home or in the country house. You sit next to the fireplace and the warm fire that you feel and see calms you. This is also possible even at work, without going anywhere.

28:51.000 --> 29:05.000
You stay in this image for a minute or two or three, come back, you will feel different. And, of course, all water images, everything related to water. Someone imagines a bubbling stream, becomes a waterfall, purely virtual.

29:05.000 --> 29:18.000
Someone imagines a small, cozy, warm swamp, I don't know, frogs quacking in the forest, and someone imagines the vastness of the ocean. Everyone has their own image.

29:35.000 --> 29:50.000
What is better, a bubbling stream or a small swamp or a vast ocean? You need to believe, trust yourself that the image that arises is needed at this moment.

29:50.000 --> 30:10.000
Another important thing. We forget that the most powerful force is in ourselves. And it is most often embedded in childhood. Each of us has good, warm, joyful situations in childhood that are useful to remember.

30:10.000 --> 30:31.000
For example, people talk about such situations. I had a very busy woman, 48 years old, she leads an institution, her own company, she has several hundred employees, three children, a husband.

30:31.000 --> 30:50.000
She has a lot of people who, frankly, watch her, she leads, they watch her, she finances her whole clan. And she said that quite often, especially when she gets very tired in the car, she is driven by a driver, she thinks about childhood.

30:50.000 --> 31:05.000
She remembers the morning when she didn't have to go to school, she remembers the morning when she woke up and her mother was baking pancakes in the kitchen.

31:05.000 --> 31:20.000
And this smell of pancakes and conversations between father and mother in the remote kitchen, in the apartment, she remembers very often because it is protection for parents, it is a free day, it is childhood.

31:20.000 --> 31:34.000
And all the intonations, good warm intonations, associated with childhood, are associated with this image. And she becomes good, quiet, calm, and she is ready to work again.

31:34.000 --> 31:51.000
One participant, a man, told another image that supports him. Back then, when there were pioneer camps, his mother often sent him to the pioneer camp, and his father and mother parted early in the morning.

31:51.000 --> 32:04.000
And his mother, as it happens wrong, but life is life, was not very happy when her father came to meet her son. And knowing this, he always came alone to the pioneer camp to meet his son.

32:04.000 --> 32:26.000
And now the father has arrived, and they began to walk around the pioneer camp, and warm, soft summer rain began. They sat down somewhere on the bench, and the father took out an umbrella, and he pressed our participant, who was already more than 40 years old, at the time when he was still small, to his father.

32:26.000 --> 32:41.000
And this soft, warm rain, a strong person close to him, and the state of calmness, of protection that he experienced then, he remembers for the rest of his life, and it gives him energy.

32:41.000 --> 32:55.000
The father is no longer in this life, but in fact, the care and strength of the father still help him. Each of us has a child's situation that gives us strength and energy.

32:55.000 --> 33:11.000
So, return to Eilers, and you will feel how protected, calm, balanced everything that was related to childhood will be again.

33:12.000 --> 33:34.000
One more exercise for completion. The authors of this exercise are boyars, husband and wife, Americans. Think about your problem now. Just think. Formulate your problem, whether it is a personal or work problem, in two or three words.

33:35.000 --> 33:50.000
My problem is... Please, remember about the person, it can be a colleague or a manager or a close person, with whom you recently discussed your problem.

33:51.000 --> 34:01.000
Remember, let it be a picture, an image. What did he say, what did you answer? Where was it? What time of day?

34:02.000 --> 34:23.000
And when this picture is already clear, take a green marker in your imagination and circle this picture, and internally get out of this circle.

34:23.000 --> 34:34.000
You, this person, manager or a close person or a colleague, everything is in a circle, the problem is in a circle, and we will now start our little psychological journey.

34:35.000 --> 34:55.000
Think about the house you live in, many apartments, many people, many neighbors. Especially, you feel it clearly when you come home in the evening, the windows are burning, and in each window there are families, people, some difficulties, difficulties or some joys in their lives.

34:56.000 --> 35:15.000
Think about it now. Think about the microdistrict or village you live in. Think about how many people surround you, and everyone has their own life with their own worries, and, to be honest, with joy and achievements.

35:15.000 --> 35:35.000
Think about the city you live in. Try to see this city from above in your image. And think about how your region is developing.

35:35.000 --> 35:52.000
Try to see a huge number of cars on the streets, people, the dynamics of this development, movement, transport. And think that each of the people who drive a car or just walk down the street also has their own life.

35:52.000 --> 36:11.000
Think about our Russia, about the northern, southern, western, eastern borders. Think about how difficult it is for this country to live now.

36:11.000 --> 36:31.000
I recently heard the phrase, Russia has been embodied in Moscow. The capital regions, not only Moscow, but any industrial regions, are now developing powerfully, perhaps, often, attracting a huge crowd of people who are forced to do business.

36:31.000 --> 36:49.000
Think about Russia and about our good optimistic prospects. We are achieving all the achievements that other countries have achieved in hundreds of years, we have been doing it for decades.

36:49.000 --> 37:17.000
Imagine that in this system there is a small planet, the blue Earth, which moves along its own trajectory.

37:17.000 --> 37:34.000
And now, when I speak, it also continues its movement. And our life on this Earth is a rather short moment, but bright, filled with the meaning of existence.

37:34.000 --> 37:53.000
Feel, please, the space, its boundlessness, its eternity as clearly as possible. And, holding the feeling of space, return to your problem.

37:53.000 --> 38:10.000
Think about your problem, which you thought about at the very beginning. Try to formulate this problem in two or three words. I am sure that the significance of your problem will be much less for you.

38:10.000 --> 38:38.000
Many people say, it's not a problem at all, it's just a difficulty, a barrier, I can overcome it. In general, in the scale of the space, it's a small, not so significant issue. And in the future of my life, it's not a problem, but a difficulty, a barrier, which will be overcome by me.

38:38.000 --> 38:49.000
Such internal journeys, images, which we have just talked about, are all visualization techniques.

38:49.000 --> 39:05.000
Of course, you felt that it was a bit of an autotraining. But it doesn't take tens of minutes, hours, two or three hours to feel that your hand is warm and heavy. We don't have time for that.

39:05.000 --> 39:19.000
And when we call a habit from our childhood or a positive image, we recover very quickly. Three, four, five minutes, not much, no more than five minutes is not necessary.

39:19.000 --> 39:38.000
Sometimes participants say, you know, I don't want to return to Earth from space. I say, you have to return. Five minutes is the maximum we can afford to wander through our inner space in order to return and start living and working again.

39:38.000 --> 39:55.000
Without stress, joyfully, optimistically, conveying your optimism to others. Our inner state really often depends on this file, the feeling of emotion.

39:55.000 --> 40:14.000
We talked about how to manage this file when external stress is imposed on us, that is, intensity, difficult meetings, aggressive negotiations with pressure to our address, or criticism from the leaders or colleagues.

40:14.000 --> 40:38.000
But there is also internal stress that we ourselves are able to strengthen. And it is reflected in this file. It is difficult for us to live emotionally when we are on this cart with a load of life problems, we also have internal problems.

40:38.000 --> 40:52.000
I mean, first of all, problems of emotional addictions. In my book, Career without Stress, there is a paragraph, the career at the cost of life.

40:52.000 --> 41:13.000
It was my client, a long-term client, with whom we had occasional meetings over the course of about three years, that is, a real professional coaching. I came to him, we discussed some situations, solved some issues, and my visit was over.

41:14.000 --> 41:31.000
And when I arrived, the client was very seriously promoted in the bank, he became the second person after the founder, after the president, the first deputy. I entered a huge office and walked to his table for a long time.

41:31.000 --> 41:44.000
And when I came up, I said, Sergey, I want to congratulate you on your success, this is really an achievement. And he said, you know, Natalia, it's very difficult for me here, I'm alone here.

41:44.000 --> 42:02.000
There, in my department, I had subordinates, almost friends, we discussed some problems together, and here there is responsibility, there should be distance, I solve some difficult financial issues, and here I am alone.

42:02.000 --> 42:16.000
Very often successful managers talk about loneliness in the profession. I said, Sergey, then why are you in this office? And he says, I prove to my father that I am strong.

42:16.000 --> 42:30.000
And I said, Sergey, is your father still alive? He says no. But still, the father was a successful official at that time, a large official, and always talked about Sergey as the only son.

42:30.000 --> 42:48.000
He said to his son, you are weak, you will not succeed. And at the peak of his father, Sergey built his career, proving to him that he was successful, that he was capable, that he was as strong as his father.

42:48.000 --> 43:07.000
Dear friends, of course, my visits to this bank became more frequent because Sergey was tired, he was burning out. He often said, you know, there is a meeting, I want to go out and walk the streets, just breathe some fresh air.

43:07.000 --> 43:33.000
His health began to deteriorate a little, and the time came, about a year and a half later, he decided to go back to the linear level, to become a linear manager from top management, to become the head of his department, to return to the life that was more optimal for him, there was less stress.

43:34.000 --> 44:01.000
A vertical career is not the only form of success. There is also a horizontal career, when a person becomes a more experienced professional, a more famous expert in their field, and rotates within the company, for example, moves to other niches, other positions, or takes other new projects, this is also a success, an achievement.

44:02.000 --> 44:27.000
A vertical career, which is connected with power, with managing people, with control, with responsibility, and often with the need for distance, loneliness, in this sense, becomes especially stressful if it is tied to solving these inner child problems, to prove to the father that I am strong.

44:28.000 --> 44:41.000
In fact, internal stress is reduced when we solve our problems correctly, related to our relationship with our parents. Everyone has them.

44:41.000 --> 45:07.000
It is considered right if the emancipation from parents, that is, our transition to adult life, begins in adolescence, at the age of 13-16, and ends at the age of 30-33, the so-called age of Christ, the first serious growth.

45:08.000 --> 45:24.000
And for men and women. Because then we begin to live our lives, then we make a career, achieving our goals and striving to realize our own values.

45:24.000 --> 45:44.000
Then we stop, if it happened, emancipation, we said no, I have my own life, my parents, we said no, I have my own goals, no, I want to work in this professional sphere, not where mom or dad says.

45:44.000 --> 45:59.000
I don't compete with my father, because a father is a father, a close person, he helped me, and most importantly, he contributed to my birth. And then it's my life path.

45:59.000 --> 46:13.000
Then we build an optimal career for ourselves, then we choose a person who is really close to us, because the influence of parents and their power is very often distributed in the personal sphere.

46:13.000 --> 46:24.000
And, by the way, most often destructive, destroying families. Then we begin to live our lives and make the right decisions.

46:43.000 --> 47:03.000
A person striving for success and a high psychological quality of life should do it on time, from 15-30 years old. Because a prolonged dependence on parents is a career worth living or health.

47:03.000 --> 47:19.000
It's hyperfictionism, we call it the excellence complex. I should be doing well, I should have only A's in school, I should be successful at work, and I meet a lot of such young ladies in all regions.

47:19.000 --> 47:32.000
Recently in Chelyabinsk, I was told in a group of successful young women, 30-35 years old, that we don't need families, we don't need children, we need a career and success.

47:32.000 --> 47:43.000
I said, you know, it's good when a woman's life, any and a man's life, is built on a balance. There is a private sphere, there is a family, there is a job. Why are you striving for success?

47:43.000 --> 47:54.000
And we found out during the discussion that, in fact, every participant is a daughter of a mother who demanded that she should be better, that she should have A's.

47:54.000 --> 48:06.000
How come you only got A's today? Look, my friend's daughter only studies for A's. Or another typical phrase for us, if you study badly, you will work as a janitor.

48:06.000 --> 48:22.000
It's a typical phrase in Russia. Or, all children are like children, and you are a child. These are the phrases of parents. These are their scenarios, which they, of course, under any positive pretext, impose on us.

48:22.000 --> 48:35.000
What does a mother say? Or a father says? More often a mother says, I care about you, because I'm a mother. Or a father says, you have to be strong, I'm strong, my son must be strong.

48:35.000 --> 48:52.000
50% is the truth of parents. But where is our next 50%? We know that parents wanted it, but entering adulthood we must realize our own desires.

48:52.000 --> 49:12.000
Let it start with the first step, 50 to 50, mom, you're right, dad, you're right, but I have my own goals, these are our 50%, my own values. I want to choose the career that I'm interested in, I choose the person I need in my life.

49:12.000 --> 49:29.000
And then our inner stress will be reduced, we will not live someone else's life. In fact, imposing your own scenario on the part of the parents is manipulating the child.

49:29.000 --> 49:48.000
It's not a secret, a mother often says, I didn't achieve it, you must achieve it. Or a father says, I didn't become this, you must become this. In fact, these are the goals and values of a father or mother.

49:48.000 --> 50:07.000
It's their life, and our life, the life of adults, must be connected with our goals and values. And when we keep our goals, we don't become a toy or a manipulation object.

50:07.000 --> 50:19.000
And this is a very important point. It often happens when a person does not grow up in time. There are many examples when a person leads a company, but internally he is not an adult.

50:19.000 --> 50:37.000
If a son depends on his mother, I always come to the company and think, where is an adult woman who really leads the company? Where is this informal leader, a gray cardinal who really leads the company?

50:37.000 --> 50:53.000
Indeed, I always find it. It can be the chief accountant, from whose opinion everything depends. It can be a lawyer who wins the trials and makes decisions.

50:53.000 --> 51:09.000
Or vice versa. If a son depends on his father, then always a more mature, experienced employee or vice-client has an influence on him.

51:09.000 --> 51:25.000
It's dangerous in business from the point of view that decisions are made with money, people, resources. The leader does not formally take decisions, he can be an founder, he invested money and has his own company.

51:25.000 --> 51:48.000
But an informal leader who manages the situation as he sees fit. It's always an internal stress for a person who is being manipulated because he always feels tension and he is uncomfortable to work and live.

51:48.000 --> 52:03.000
It's always, to be honest, offensive and unfair because it's like they take away a part of life or a part of work.

52:03.000 --> 52:29.000
I would like to finish the analysis of this question with the following phrase. Live your life and then you will not have exhausting, uncomfortable internal stress, which is due to the fact that a person strives to be independent all his life, but he does not succeed.

52:30.000 --> 52:40.000
Another question related to this important file of feelings, emotions and experiences is asked in groups very often.

52:40.000 --> 52:51.000
When people say, ok, Natalia, we understand everything, these images help to switch for 2, 3, 4, 5 minutes, it's like a little rest, time out.

52:51.000 --> 53:05.000
But if it's not enough for me, it doesn't help me at all, I've been doing it for a long time, and even in traffic jams I can turn off, look at the sky and see what good clouds, how great it is, what good weather.

53:05.000 --> 53:24.000
And yet after a while, 5, 10, 15 minutes, I feel the accumulated fatigue again. What to do? Of course, here this principle, the main technique of break, time out, switching remains relevant.

53:24.000 --> 53:46.000
The only thing is that it needs to be done in real life and more prolonged. Now not those long vacations that used to be once a year for 2-3 weeks or twice a year for 2 weeks, but people began to take mini-vacations for 5-7 days and go somewhere.

53:46.000 --> 54:03.000
It is important to completely change the situation. It can be from the capital city to the village where you need to carry water, heat the stove, clean the snow around the house.

54:03.000 --> 54:22.000
A wonderful village life, a healthy village life, or a trip to the warm sea, or mountain skiing, or a wellness hotel or spa hotel.

54:22.000 --> 54:38.000
Who loves what? Please decide in your mini-vacation what you like best. Passive relaxation, wellness and spa procedures, or vice versa, drive, excitement, extreme.

54:38.000 --> 55:00.000
It can be rafting, parachute jumping, extreme driving. Everyone has their own choice. It is important that we allow ourselves to rest and switch 4 times a year with a good company or a close person.

55:00.000 --> 55:17.000
With such a positive communication. But it is important that when you return you feel completely renewed. Do it as a way of your life, as a rule.

55:17.000 --> 55:36.000
Then you will feel that every time you wash off the accumulated stress. Do not tighten, do not accumulate stress so that it is overfilled with a bowl. Then you will really need to take a prolonged rest.

55:36.000 --> 55:56.000
But we don't have time for that. So, a vacation 3-4 times a year. The vacation you like, the vacation you can afford financially. This is the best thing you can recommend now to quickly release the accumulated stress.

55:56.000 --> 56:19.000
There is another file that we must talk about. This is our unconscious. If you remember Freud's main idea, he said that a person only thinks that he is consciously and purposefully making decisions and doing things.

56:19.000 --> 56:42.000
In fact, it is a game of his unconscious. And a person only interprets, evaluates, analyzes what has come out. Or another image that Freud drew for us. He said that our unconscious is a flying horse.

56:43.000 --> 56:59.000
And we are only a rider with our will and consciousness that pulls the leash, trying to set the course for the moving animal.

56:59.000 --> 57:15.000
If we translate it into modern language, probably the unconscious content in our inner world, in this biocomputer, is 60-70-80%. This is really huge content.

57:15.000 --> 57:30.000
What is there? First, it is our genetic memory. These are the scenarios, maybe the family tasks that our ancestors have given us.

57:30.000 --> 57:46.000
There are such laws, they are called universal laws, which express, reflect, and record these contents. In particular, there is a law of synchronization.

57:46.000 --> 57:59.000
We often repeat events in our fate, and they are even reflected in the numbers, for example, birth, marriage, departure from life of our ancestors.

57:59.000 --> 58:21.000
We often repeat the actions of our ancestors. We often complete the tasks that were set before our grandfathers, grandmothers and great-grandfathers, great-grandmothers, but which they did not complete for one reason or another.

58:21.000 --> 58:38.000
This is our genetic memory. Another content that is very much in the unconscious is our impressions. Not only positive, as we said a little in childhood, but also difficult, tense.

58:38.000 --> 58:53.000
It can be a feeling of loneliness in the room of a small child, or a feeling of fear, a child who is being thrown by a barking dog. I tell all the specific examples from my consultations.

58:53.000 --> 59:12.000
For example, a leader who was afraid and reacted uncomfortably to a cry, we analyzed his path and came to the conclusion that this is the 4-year-old age and his experience at this age when a barking dog threw at him.

59:12.000 --> 59:22.000
These are really some impressions, fragments of impressions, quite often traumatic, which we received in childhood.

59:22.000 --> 59:45.000
Our unconscious is also a scenario that we ourselves think through, try, from which we refuse. And our unconscious is also our desire to enjoy life.

59:45.000 --> 01:00:01.000
In general, if we sum it up, we need not be afraid of the unconscious at all. If we sum it up, we need to say that our unconscious loves pleasure. Our unconscious is drawn to acceptance and love.

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:15.000
And then what is the conclusion? How to use this file to reduce stress? Please think that our unconscious is really dissatisfied with something.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:32.000
When you get up in the morning and seem to have said positive phrases, or you come to the mirror and return to positive images, and still something is not good, something is not liked, it seems to be some kind of misfortune, it is not clear why.

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:50.000
It is not clear why, but it is our unconscious. What should be done to calm this strange, incomprehensible file, part of our existence?

01:00:50.000 --> 01:01:03.000
The first thing we should think about. Every day, even if it is a small event, but you need to think about doing something pleasant to yourself.

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:17.000
You wake up in the morning. Tell me, please, what will be pleasant for me today? Yes, there will be work, there will be meetings with colleagues.

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:34.000
Maybe in the evening you will go to buy something for yourself, a small shopping, but very interesting. A man may come and buy an interesting DVD, a woman may buy a small souvenir or something from cosmetics.

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:56.000
I had one participant who said, Natalia, if you came to my house and went into my bathroom, you would say that this is a chemical laboratory. I come after work and immediately remember that I go to the bathroom, and there I have different creams, lotions, I take care of myself, and it is a pleasure for me.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:02:13.000
Here she has a bath, it is not a chemical laboratory, it is a small spa hotel where she enjoys herself. It can be any hobbies, hobbies that help a person calm down.

01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:26.000
It can be home flowers. There was one participant who said, I come to the apartment and I need at least an hour and a half to water each flower, but I am in a good mood.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:43.000
Other participants said, well, okay, they don't talk, so we are in a good mood, we are getting rid of communicative stress. Yes, it is certainly true, but it is a hobby, where a person enjoys, calms him down unconsciously.

01:02:43.000 --> 01:03:00.000
Now it has become fashionable, in a good sense of the word, business fashion, accepted among successful people to be involved in something else. Someone starts drawing, I will return to this again, it is a calming of one's unconscious.

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:18.000
Someone starts collecting. It is very important, among other things, for the unconscious, that someone next to us treats us very well. It is great, it is lucky in life if someone sincerely loves us.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:37.000
But if it did not happen for one reason or another, then a small pet, a cat or a dog, is also one of the techniques, if I may say so, to calm our unconscious.

01:03:37.000 --> 01:03:57.000
I remember one of the cases that I had in one of the companies. I came to the company to do a pre-training diagnosis. The head said, please find a conflict person. I felt tension between the units, I felt some kind of discomfort.

01:03:57.000 --> 01:04:13.000
I said, maybe you will tell me who starts the conflicts. I talked to many people, it was 27 people, and it turned out that one of the employees was a very tense and conflicting person.

01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:29.000
When we started talking to her, it turned out that she was a lady, over 40 years old, nothing happened, it happens in life. She has no children, no marriages, and she lives alone. She has a cat, whose name is Musya.

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:48.000
When she tries to tell something about her family at corporate parties or in the corner of conversations, as others do, and she tells about her family, and her family includes her and her cat, everyone laughs at it.

01:04:48.000 --> 01:05:05.000
I had enough to talk to several people in this company, informal people who asked a ton of public opinion, that the cat Musya is the creature that accepts, loves its owner.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:25.000
It is very important to respect another woman's fate and listen to her admiration for this cat or her story. Because it is as important as a story about a child, a husband or a wife.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:34.000
As a result, she was involved in communication in the company, and the conflicts were exhausted.

01:05:55.000 --> 01:06:13.000
The first thing is a hobby, a hobby, a little pleasure. This must be included in the plan of our day. And in general, when we write a list of things, in the evening, be sure to schedule a time.

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:34.000
For example, I talk to my son for 30 minutes. If I can, an hour and a half, it will be even better. In the evening I will buy myself a Toto. I will spend 40 minutes in communication with pleasant friends.

01:06:35.000 --> 01:06:52.000
It must be a position, a point in your work plan that allows you to maintain your ability to work at a high level and that allows you to calm our unconscious sphere.

01:06:52.000 --> 01:07:07.000
The second point is that there must be hobbies and time spent on them in order to feel a sense of pleasure. It can be drawing, it can be singing.

01:07:07.000 --> 01:07:20.000
For example, many people are engaged in singing. It can be mastering a musical instrument. This is also very good now. Imagine a corporate party, you come out of the guitar and start singing something. Your status changes.

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:37.000
People see you from the other side. You sing the song you chose. This is part of your image. I assure you that a month or a month and a half after the corporate party you will be popular in the company or in the department.

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:59.000
You take pictures, make a vernissage of your own photos for a corporate party and hang them on one of the walls and people will start talking about you too. You can become popular, successful and join the contacts and communications in your department or company with your hobby and passion.

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:24.000
Moreover, you can find out that other colleagues have the same interests. Someone is also engaged in photography, someone is raising pets, someone is engaged in singing, someone is engaged in musical instruments. Imagine how many new friends you can get in your office and how you can improve, make your business contacts more effective.

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:37.000
We remember that the principle of pleasure, hobby and passion are important for our unconscious. And the feeling of freedom that we get only in creativity.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:54.000
There is another file that we haven't talked about. You see, it is at the base of our scheme. I called it the body. It is our psychophysics, our physicality.

01:08:54.000 --> 01:09:13.000
And there are also laws. You probably noticed that when chronic burnout occurs, such exhausting, constant, long-term stress, then the head starts to hurt, colds are cleared.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:24.000
Our well-being is really deteriorating. This is already affected by psychosomatic. It is a dangerous symptom.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:46.000
If we positively perceive ourselves and others, if we have learned to regulate our emotions, if we understand what our unconscious needs, then we should not forget that a healthy lifestyle is also our basic competence.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:10:01.000
