01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:19.000
I remember a company in Moscow that, moving to another new office, agreed with the employees that they allocate only one place in the company, between the second and third floors, where you can really get together and smoke a cigarette.

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:39.000
I know of a company that specifies the time you can spend on smoking. I remember the case of the corporate standard in this company, which is formulated approximately like this.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:11:01.000
You can smoke for three minutes before lunch and only three minutes after lunch. Moreover, in solitude, not with someone else in the company. Because we know that when we are with someone else, we start talking, that it is 2, 3, 5 cigarettes, maybe not 3 minutes, but 5, 15, 20 minutes.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:15.000
Now in offices, in many companies, they control the time that is allocated for smoking. And not only because it is paid time, and nothing is done during this time.

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:40.000
I agree with this, maybe it is right. But smoking itself is an unhealthy lifestyle. And companies try to regulate the time spent on it, and even take away a certain place.

01:11:40.000 --> 01:12:02.000
The fact remains that there are companies that do not even allow their employees to smoke in the office. Moreover, already in Moscow, there are companies in our Russian cities where you can not smoke for your employees even near the office.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:19.000
I think that such an official corporate policy of fighting smoking may not be liked by everyone. But this is a reflection of the cult of a healthy lifestyle that we are forced to support if we want to be successful.

01:12:19.000 --> 01:12:37.000
My observations are interesting. If you go to an elite village, consult, for example, I often go, and it happens that I go very early, at 8 or 9 am, and you see a lot of people running around the village who are engaged in a healthy lifestyle.

01:12:37.000 --> 01:12:59.000
And in the morning, recently, I had an impression that the president of a company was running around with his wife, and they were sweating, and a car was following them, and there was a guard in a white shirt and tie. It looked interesting.

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:22.000
But the fact remains that people thought about being healthy. And if we go to the outskirts of the city and see a not very elite area, we will return at 12 o'clock, and people just leave their homes, worn out, not sleeping, and immediately have cigarettes in their teeth.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:40.000
And I see that successful people get up early, run, give up smoking, and people who said no, life goes on and on, they do not lead a healthy lifestyle. A healthy lifestyle is our important basic competence.

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:56.000
It's not just a long-term dream, a refusal to smoke and excessive alcohol, but also the right way to spend the day. Dear friends, let's think about how to live our day right.

01:13:56.000 --> 01:14:12.000
We wake up in the morning, it's wrong to rush out of bed and shout that you're late or you're late, that you need to hurry. Please get up 15-20 minutes earlier.

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:25.000
For the body, 15-20 minutes of lack of sleep does not mean anything. But they will give you an opportunity not to rush from the very beginning of the day.

01:14:25.000 --> 01:14:43.000
I always look sadly in traffic jams when people start to turn the wheel of the car to make it in time, especially when I'm driving. I see a car that is being cut and I drive up to it and look to the right.

01:14:43.000 --> 01:15:06.000
I always look at the owner of the car with pleasure because we drove up on time, he still did not win these 15-20 minutes. I always look at the car as a specialist.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:18.000
Sometimes I look at my neighbor as a specialist on the 4th floor trying to start the car, especially in the cold days. He can't do it, he runs around because he's in a hurry.

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:34.000
Every time I think, why did you get up 15-20 minutes later? Because you need to hurry, and hurrying is stress. The time limit, hurrying, when we lack time, when time is pressed, we need to know what it is.

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:53.000
One of the most important stress factors, one of the dominant stress factors. Moreover, let's go back to our morning. We just woke up. Your alarm clock, as Rick Bray says, should sound quiet and gentle.

01:15:53.000 --> 01:16:03.000
Because the alarm clock, the phone call is the same stress factor as an electric shock. On the carpet, they are not dangerous for life, but very unpleasant.

01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:21.000
So, if we start the day in a hurry, we start the day with stress. Get up early so as not to hurry. If we start the day with a sharp sound, make sure that there is no sharp sound at the beginning of the day. Then there will be no stress.

01:16:21.000 --> 01:16:39.000
The beginning of the day with a stressful state is a program of stress during the whole day. So, you got up. Good, you are not in a hurry. You move around the apartment slowly enough, getting ready for work.

01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:57.000
Be kind. Start the day with the pleasure we talked about, nourishing your unconsciousness. Dress in a color that is pleasant for you. Let it be a bright color. Someone likes yellow. It is really warm.

01:16:57.000 --> 01:17:14.000
In general, for Slavs, yellow is the color of the sun, warmth, coming spring. Someone likes red. It is also a great color for us because it is energy, it is a rise of the spirit.

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:29.000
Someone likes blue. Especially emotional people like blue because it disciplines. And someone likes green, because for irritable people it is the color that calms.

01:17:29.000 --> 01:17:47.000
Dress in the color you like. Eat something delicious that you like. And slowly, without hurrying, get out of the house. If you drive, try to find routes so that you do not get stuck in a traffic jam.

01:17:47.000 --> 01:18:03.000
If you get stuck in a traffic jam, think about positive images. If you are driving on public transport, go to the areas of your path where you meet positive people. You know that a woman always smiles in a kiosk. Ask her questions.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:13.000
Exchange impressions of the day, jokes, smiles, and you will feel that your mood is rising.

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:36.000
You came to the office. Friends, please, do not start the day with discussing the sports achievements of your favorite team or, as it happens among women, discussing what terrible happened in the family the previous evening.

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:52.000
The son got a two, the husband said an unfair word. It is not necessary. Discussing sports achievements can take up to an hour and a half. Discussing husbands and children is also a long time.

01:18:52.000 --> 01:19:08.000
But the fact remains that we start with either a very driving or not very pleasant topic. The right start of the day. Take the bull by the horns. Do your work right away, priority business.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:32.000
It will give you a sense of calm, the right program. Moreover, it is even recommended to eat a raw frog. Do an unpleasant but priority business.

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:42.000
Why? To reduce your own stress. To say to yourself, great, I have already overcome my unwillingness. And the day will go on very well.

01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:58.000
Priority business, even unpleasant, will give us an opportunity to use the fresh brain in the morning to solve serious problems.

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:10.000
You have done an important thing. You can rest. Do not forget about rest. Three or five minutes between tasks is very important. Naturally, we have come to lunchtime.

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:28.000
Everyone knows that it is bad and wrong to have a snack at work. It is so. Do not do this. Everyone knows that you need to have lunch for at least 30 minutes. Do not shorten your lunch to 15 minutes or 10-15 minutes of snacking at work.

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:43.000
In addition to the fact that you are doing it wrong in terms of health, but if we talk about our well-being, about stress, we just do not have time to calm down during lunchtime.

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:55.000
But you need to calm down. Imagine, we went to a cafe or a restaurant, especially in a business center. It is present next to our company or in your company.

01:20:55.000 --> 01:21:08.000
We start to have a full lunch. We switched to taste sensations. We talked to colleagues. Everyone knows that a good lunch calms you down.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:27.000
Even if the beginning of the day was tense, after lunch, people usually feel calmer and more balanced. Moreover, experienced clients know that if we call a VIP client, a large client, it is better to call right after lunch.

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:43.000
A person usually feels good. The working day goes on. What is the right way to end a working day if we talk about healthy style of behavior in the office? Of course, it is to sum up.

01:21:43.000 --> 01:22:03.000
The feeling of completion, that I did something important during the day, is an amazing pleasure. I have seen happy people in the office who take lists, if the program or plan of the day is a vote-look, they print out a list of work.

01:22:03.000 --> 01:22:23.000
And they happily, with colorful markers, mark what was done. It gives a feeling of completion, that the day was not in vain. Moreover, green markers are often highlighted with priority cases, and red ones with small cases.

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:34.000
And then they look at how many important tasks were done and how many small ones. They try to reduce small cases and increase the number of important priority cases.

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:49.000
After such a good end of the day, you need to remember that there is a dead zone. Please leave the office at the time that is officially recorded by the company.

01:22:49.000 --> 01:23:04.000
18.00 or 19.00. It is called the dead zone. Share your life, this is the right healthy lifestyle, in two halves. The first half is work, profession. The second half is private life.

01:23:04.000 --> 01:23:21.000
This is the right healthy lifestyle, this is an antistress program, support, if there is such an individually found balance of work and home.

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:41.000
Because if only home, we know it, it is routine, monotony, if we do not work, especially in women's fate, it happens sometimes, a woman does not work, it is domestic depression, it is routine, monotony, it is the same, repetitive, sometimes boring things.

01:23:41.000 --> 01:24:01.000
But if we only work, so-called workaholism, and now, unfortunately, not only men, as before, but also women began to say, well, Natalia, I leave in the morning, my children, women, I emphasize, are still sleeping, and when I come, they are already sleeping.

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:14.000
This is also a wrong lifestyle, because it is a squirrel in a wheel, it is all the energy, all our talents and gifts are given to work.

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:31.000
It is bright colors, bright emotions at work, and gray, boring, something at home, it happens very often. Or in general, a person comes home very late, after the dead zone.

01:24:31.000 --> 01:24:49.000
I remember that tourist company where we did stress management training, and the wise manager on the flip chart drew the time 19.00 and wrote the dead zone, we are leaving the office.

01:24:49.000 --> 01:25:09.000
And then she asked the security guard to bypass the office and offer people to go home. After a while she called me and said, Natalia, I even pay security if she turns off the electricity so that computers do not work, so that people go home.

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:23.000
Unfortunately, I have to go back to this case. About a few months later, the manager called me and said, Natalia, in fact, I did not succeed, because people transfer their work home.

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:40.000
They have computers and they work at home. I came to this company and said, why did we agree on the dead zone, it is a healthy lifestyle. And one of the participants said, Natalia, you know, somewhere around 10 pm my mother calls and says, go home. I do not listen.

01:25:40.000 --> 01:25:59.000
Then my son calls, I do not listen. Then my husband calls, it's already 1 am, I do not listen. But when they bring the phone to my beloved dog, she starts making sounds on the phone, then I get in the car and go home.

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:19.000
Of course, I agree, we work a lot. But still, especially in the second half of life, when a person summarizes, he first of all talks about children, family, his clan, so to speak.

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:29.000
And he remembers those years when he could not divide his life into two halves, and most of it was spent on work, and most often he regrets it.

01:26:29.000 --> 01:26:44.000
Not to mention that, especially in the pre-pension and retirement age, and especially men, they do not know how to live if life was really devoted only to work.

01:26:44.000 --> 01:26:59.000
Because the feature that is associated with retirement for a workaholic, first of all men, but now it becomes a workaholic and women, is associated with the question, how can I live without work?

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:13.000
And in fact, if we take a Western lifestyle, a healthy lifestyle, many Western people say, adults, mature people, when I leave work, life is just beginning.

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:30.000
I start traveling, doing some of the activities that I have postponed for a long time, and they meet this part of their life with joy only because there was no exhausting stressful workaholism for a long time.

01:27:30.000 --> 01:27:47.000
So we have a dead zone, 18 or 19 hours. Be kind, carefully fold your papers, you have completed the day, emphasize what has been done, and come home with joy and pleasure.

01:27:47.000 --> 01:28:06.000
The only thing from the perspective of a healthy lifestyle, an antistress lifestyle, I would like to say, when you knock on the door or open the door of your house or apartment, make a happy face.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:25.000
Because very often people say, especially women, although this is typical for men, if a person came tired, stressed, tense, it would be better if he came late when we were all asleep, so as not to see his face.

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:37.000
Moreover, I will now tell you an example that was highlighted in one of the trainings, but not one participant said, I often say, a man comes home tired, irritated, and says, not a fact.

01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:50.000
You know, I have a wife and two sons, when my wife comes home, I always shout to my sons, guys, close the door, mom has come. Everyone asked why.

01:28:50.000 --> 01:29:06.000
Because she comes irritated, unhappy, she immediately says that she did not succeed at work, who competes with her, and, frankly, it's very hard. I would also like to communicate in peace in the house after work.

01:29:06.000 --> 01:29:26.000
This does not happen, and therefore we close for 15-20 minutes. I say, why for 15-20 minutes? Because, he says, our pet dog runs out to meet her. And all her accumulated office aggression, her office stress is thrown at the dog.

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:46.000
I say, what is she doing? She scolds, says something to our pet dog. And after 15-20 minutes, I know from experience that she is calm now. And I always shout to my sons, kids, guys, everything is fine, you can go out.

01:29:46.000 --> 01:29:59.000
A slightly funny case, anecdotal, a fact remains a fact, we can all remember our life situations when it was exactly the same when we come home irritated.

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:12.000
We don't need to do this, both men and women. The family is the leading key antistress resource in our life. We lick our wounds there, we rest there.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:33.000
We can say that there is our refuge. And therefore everyone in this space needs it, but they are also able to help us to recover, calm down, feel that our life is safe, that we are thriving.

01:30:34.000 --> 01:30:48.000
And if we will release our stress irritation on close people, this antistress resource will not work, will stop working. Indeed, the child will avoid us, he will look out, see an irritated mother or father and hide.

01:30:48.000 --> 01:31:02.000
The spouse or wife will do the same and our family contacts will be violated. So, a healthy lifestyle is the right start of the day.

01:31:02.000 --> 01:31:15.000
A healthy lifestyle is the absence of hurry, it is desirable to eliminate stress factors, especially at the beginning of the day.

01:31:16.000 --> 01:31:30.000
A healthy lifestyle and a healthy style of behavior in the office is to perform priority tasks at the beginning of the day to feel satisfaction, so as not to hurry later.

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:56.000
A healthy lifestyle is a full lunch, it is right to leave work in time with a healthy style of behavior in the office, having successfully completed your day and having given part of your time to family affairs.

01:31:57.000 --> 01:32:17.000
You can ask me, is it all regulated? Will I lead a healthy lifestyle if I regulate everything? Indeed, one of my participants wrote to me, Natalia, I do everything on my day, Saturday and Sunday, and I have time to do everything, but for some reason I have little happiness.

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:46.000
I must say, and this is also a healthy and joyful way of thinking and emotionally lifestyle, be kind, regulate your working day, your working week so as to completely free Saturday and Sunday and not make any regulations, but live these free days with your loved ones as you wish.

01:32:47.000 --> 01:33:00.000
You will not hurry, you will go somewhere, you will communicate with children, you will listen to what your child says, and he will say very wise things.

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:15.000
You will sit in the family circle in the evening in front of the TV, turning on some positive programs, and it will be all right, and this is also a healthy lifestyle.

01:33:15.000 --> 01:33:25.000
But the biggest stress, the deepest, begins when our top floor is burning and burning.

01:33:25.000 --> 01:33:50.000
This is the spirit of our spirituality, part of our soul, and you see it depicted here at the very top. This is what is connected with our values, goals, meanings, scenarios, with our construction of our life and fate, which we ourselves carry out.

01:33:51.000 --> 01:34:05.000
People are divided into two categories. There are internals who set goals and strive to achieve them, and there are externals who adapt to the circumstances.

01:34:05.000 --> 01:34:22.000
Internals say, I set a goal, I achieved it, this is my achievement, this is my failure. They are usually more optimistic and energetic, and, by the way, more satisfied, especially in the second half of their lives, because they draw positive conclusions.

01:34:22.000 --> 01:34:43.000
And externals are usually inclined to pessimism, to fatalities, they say, fate, circumstances, time. They are more predisposed to sadness and very often, especially in the second half of their lives, are not satisfied with the results they have.

01:34:43.000 --> 01:35:03.000
They have, but the time has already passed. Externals often say that opportunities are lost. And internals, on the contrary, say that every moment of life is another opportunity.

01:35:03.000 --> 01:35:22.000
Choose the style that you like. I say that an internal approach to life is more beneficial for us, because then we are really able to self-realize.

01:35:22.000 --> 01:35:36.000
Then we can really satisfy our need for self-realization, which Abraham Maslow spoke about in the last century and which is very close to us now.

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:51.000
How to do it? In order to understand, determine, realize your values and your meaning, try to answer such questions.

01:35:51.000 --> 01:36:11.000
Imagine that now you can choose any historical time in the past. What time would you choose? You are interested. And who would you imagine yourself in this time?

01:36:11.000 --> 01:36:29.000
Perhaps someone chooses antiquity and this freedom of dialogue. Perhaps someone chooses... I recently heard in a group that one of the participants said,

01:36:29.000 --> 01:36:48.000
I am Elizaveta, that is, the royal court and some sophisticated relations in this court. Someone chooses the estate and the economy in this estate. Think, please, historical time and who you are in this time.

01:36:48.000 --> 01:37:02.000
By the way, if you are a woman, it is not a fact that you will choose a woman's role. Maybe you will see your male role. If you are a man, it is not a fact that you will choose a male role. Maybe you will see some female existence.

01:37:02.000 --> 01:37:23.000
Analysis of such an image allows you to feel your second, or maybe some additional, self and to push for some value, some goal that you did not think about before.

01:37:24.000 --> 01:37:44.000
In general, if we talk about this very top floor of spirituality, it is our illusion that this floor consists only of one self. There are many selves, many different selves, many different beginnings.

01:37:45.000 --> 01:38:03.000
And the fullness of life of the inmates is often due to the fact that they are able to move from one self to another. Think, please, now about the future time and who you are in this time if you choose the future.

01:38:03.000 --> 01:38:23.000
What are you doing? How do you look? How do you feel? Maybe it is a spaceship to another planet. Or maybe it is the other way around. It is the earthly existence. It is also a part of our self.

01:38:24.000 --> 01:38:41.000
Another very important question. Imagine that you have a magician in front of you and she says, I will fulfill the most important of your wishes, which, as you think, is now unnecessary.

01:38:41.000 --> 01:39:06.000
What wish would be relevant for you? Our spirituality, our goals, values and meanings are very acute. We feel it in our teenage years. It is 10, 12, 15, 18 years. This is also the end of the teenage years, the beginning of youth.

01:39:06.000 --> 01:39:17.000
But then we forget it successfully. We start to agree with others. We are told that you cannot do this, you are not capable of this, no one can do this.

01:39:18.000 --> 01:39:31.000
But now, when I ask this question, it will be very good if you remember your teenage dreams.

01:39:31.000 --> 01:39:47.000
We already know that if we build a program of our life, believing that this is our gift, it will happen, it will be successful, it will be updated, it will happen.

01:39:47.000 --> 01:40:01.000
If we say, no, I can't do anything, I'm a weak person, I have circumstances, then it won't happen. We build our own program.

01:40:01.000 --> 01:40:19.000
Now in the groups many say that the phrase of Paolo Coeli has been remembered, if you really want, the whole universe will go against you, it will come true.

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:46.000
Our file, which is connected with spirituality, will really give us an opportunity to overcome this deep exhausting stress, which is connected with the loss of meaning, work and life, when we make our life to realize our value or our goal.

01:40:46.000 --> 01:41:02.000
So, you chose the historical time, you determined an unfulfilled dream, and when we started talking about it, you thought, why is it unfulfilled, it can be realized.

01:41:02.000 --> 01:41:13.000
Moreover, now more and more people are starting to change their profession, not only at 30-35, but at 40-45, to another professional sphere.

01:41:13.000 --> 01:41:30.000
As the great Freud said, every person has 7 geniuses, 7 gifts, and we can make only one life.

01:41:30.000 --> 01:41:46.000
Many of us are already trying to make two of our gifts, three, maybe four. It's all the fullness of existence and the reduction of stress, dissatisfaction with ourselves on this file, on the file of spirituality.

01:41:46.000 --> 01:41:58.000
You are interested, then we will move on. Write a fairy tale about your life. What is a fairy tale?

01:41:58.000 --> 01:42:22.000
It's some kind of beginning. There is a main character or heroine who has set some goals, there is some route. And, of course, there are bad, evil forces that prevent you from achieving this route, to realize this route and achieve the goals.

01:42:22.000 --> 01:42:41.000
Describe, please, how you fight against these bad forces, how you win, what you do. Any fairy tale ends with a happy ending, a good, positive, victorious result.

01:42:41.000 --> 01:42:59.000
In fact, through such a fairy tale you can see your life in one image, moreover, you can write down, program your success.

01:42:59.000 --> 01:43:14.000
I had a very respectable person in one of the groups. He came to the stress management with two guards. They were behind him. And he also wrote a fairy tale.

01:43:14.000 --> 01:43:31.000
Before writing it, he was surprised. He said, Natalia, why do I need this? I have 1,200 people under me. And he looked at me harshly. But when he started writing the fairy tale, after a while his face smoothed out, he calmed down.

01:43:31.000 --> 01:43:50.000
And when he finished his story, he shook my hand and said, thank you very much, I made a decision. Of course, I didn't know what decision he made. There is no need to ask. There is business. There are a lot of questions that should be closed for an external consultant.

01:43:50.000 --> 01:44:06.000
But the fact remains. Through this fairy tale, through this holistic narrative, apparently, he determined a goal for himself that he had to reach.

01:44:06.000 --> 01:44:20.000
If you feel insecure, depressed, and feel that you are losing the purpose and meaning of your existence again, maybe you will write a story about your heroic past.

01:44:20.000 --> 01:44:37.000
A story about a heroic past is also a description, a fixation of your goals and values. Describe where you started. For example, the company started working on the basement floor. It's called beautifully.

01:44:37.000 --> 01:44:52.000
There were three people in the basement. Look at the result. Now there are 300 people in the company. Two floors of this business center are yours. There were several clients then. Now there are dozens of clients.

01:44:52.000 --> 01:45:07.000
There were such turnovers then. Now you are proudly saying large numbers. Then there was only the central office in your city. Now there is a territorial representation and you have turned into a holding.

01:45:07.000 --> 01:45:25.000
This description or discussion also gives an opportunity to push again for your goal, value, and meaning of your office career or private existence.

01:45:25.000 --> 01:45:48.000
Another exercise, an offer. Imagine yourself at 70 years old. This is a good age. You still have the ability to work, vitality, good health, but most of your life is already behind.

01:45:48.000 --> 01:46:03.000
This is the so-called golden age when the results are drawn. Regardless of how old you are now, imagine yourself on this day, at this hour, in the future when you are 70 years old.

01:46:03.000 --> 01:46:24.000
It would be great if you could see where you are, who is around you, how you look, and what you are doing. I would not want you to see yourself in the office, surrounded by colleagues or subordinates.

01:46:25.000 --> 01:46:38.000
It is a very long office job, life. I would like you to see yourself among your loved ones, maybe on a trip.

01:46:38.000 --> 01:47:00.000
Think, please, from the position of a 70-year-old man, what is important, valuable, leading in your existence now, for him, who is already wise.

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:20.000
When you think about yourself at 70, what will you highlight? Will you regret something? Will you be delighted with something?

01:47:20.000 --> 01:47:44.000
Try to highlight priorities, important, serious values, that will give you vitality up to 70 years old. You will not devalue them yourself at 70. You will say, yes, I spent my life on this.

01:47:44.000 --> 01:48:04.000
Another very interesting and important technique. Take a clean sheet of paper. Especially when you do not have enough time and energy.

01:48:04.000 --> 01:48:30.000
And when there is acute dissatisfaction, and you feel that this dissatisfaction is associated with values, divide the clean sheet of paper into two halves. And on the left, write the lesson from the position, I must or I must.

01:48:31.000 --> 01:48:42.000
The first, the second, and so on. It can be 12 positions, it can be 2 positions, it can be 42 positions, as many as you want.

01:48:42.000 --> 01:48:57.000
So what are you doing now? At the moment, from the position, I must or I must. Your debts. You force yourself. You say, I must work well, I must be a good father, I must be a good husband, and so on.

01:48:58.000 --> 01:49:21.000
